send_task sends a task command to the network.

It is an application that is part of Tenet Distribution
( http://tenet.usc.edu )

This application is useful to play/test constructing task.

Construction a task
-------------------
Instructions for constructing a task (which is, writing a task description)
can be found at docs/Tasking_API.HOWT

You can also try ./send_task -a

RUN
----
./send_task "string_task"

For example:
./send_task "set_leds('7')"
./send_task "wait(500,1)->count(5,0,1)->set_leds(5)->send()"

HELP
----
./send_task -h

